quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  26,160,The people of Lot impugned the apostles
  26,161,"when Lot, their brother, said to them, ‘Will you not be wary [of Allah]"
  26,162,"Indeed I am a trusted apostle [sent] to you"
  26,163,So be wary of Allah and obey me
  26,164,I do not ask you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of all the worlds
  26,165,What! Of all people do you come to males
  26,166,"abandoning your wives your Lord has created for you? Indeed, you are a transgressing lot.’"
  26,167,"They said, ‘Lot, if you do not desist, you will surely be banished.’"
  26,168,"He said, ‘Indeed I detest your conduct.’"
  26,169,‘My Lord! Deliver me and my family from what they do.’
  26,170,So We delivered him and all his family
  26,171,except an old woman who remained behind
  26,172,"Then We destroyed [all] the rest"
  26,173,"and rained down upon them a rain [of stones]. Evil was the rain of those who were warned"
  26,174,There is indeed a sign in that; but most of them do not have faith
  26,175,"Indeed your Lord is the All-mighty, the All-merciful"
  26,176,The inhabitants of Aykah impugned the apostles
  26,177,"when Shu‘ayb said to them, ‘Will you not be wary [of Allah]"
  26,178,"Indeed I am a trusted apostle [sent] to you"
  26,179,So be wary of Allah and obey me
  26,180,I do not ask you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of all the worlds
  26,181,"Observe the full measure, and do not be of those who give short measure"
  26,182,Weigh with an even balance
  26,183,"and do not cheat the people of their goods. Do not act wickedly on the earth, causing corruption"